Now let me reason through each fix:

**Fix 1 (Line 27):** `variant="plain"` — The type changed to add `'stateful'` to the union, but `"plain"` is still a valid value in the new type. This value is unchanged and still valid. **No change needed.**

**Fix 2 (Line 22):** Icon children should be moved to the `icon` prop. Currently the `<Button>` has `<CloseIcon />` as its only child. Per the rule, when a Button contains only an icon element, move it to the `icon` prop and make the element self-closing:

Before:
```jsx
<Button
  aria-label={ariaLabel || t('Close')}
  className={classNames('co-close-button', additionalClassName)}
  data-test-id={dataTestID}
  onClick={onClick}
  variant="plain"
>
  <CloseIcon />
</Button>
```

After:
```jsx
<Button
  aria-label={ariaLabel || t('Close')}
  className={classNames('co-close-button', additionalClassName)}
  data-test-id={dataTestID}
  onClick={onClick}
  variant="plain"
  icon={<CloseIcon />}
/>
```

The `CloseIcon` import is still needed (it's used in the `icon` prop), so no import changes needed.

